<abstract><t>This document describes the use of a well-known Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) community for destination based blackholing in IP networks.  This well-known advisory transitive BGP community, namely BLACKHOLE, allows an origin AS to specify that a neighboring network should discard any traffic destined towards the tagged IP prefix.</t></abstract>

